Eva María Pérez Fernández

Game Designer in progress

PORTFOLIO

Necrognomicon

Third-person action-tower defense game about smashing hordes of evil garden gnomes! In this project I took care of the whole design department, designing every system in the game: AI, horde manager, combat, weapons, narrative, levels and so on. Available on: our team's itch.io page!

Gatecrasher

Gatecrasher is a tower defense I designed for an university project. Use St. Peter's troops to defend heaven against the attack of several sinners! Available here

RIP

RIP is an arcade game made for Student Game Jam VI. Stop the evil reapers from taking the elderly's souls and try to score as many points as possible! Available here

Balaclava

Balaclava is an asymmetrical multiplayer game about robbing banks I designed for an university project. One of the players has to break into the bank and the other one will have access to a database with crucial information for the robbery to be successful. Together they'll have to solve puzzles, avoid guards, open safes and steal the cash! Available here

IFO

IFO is an arcade game I designed for a game jam. Themewas ridiculous superpowers, so we made a game about fighting alien dogs by throwing them deadly slippers and putting a super-powerful sleepwalker baby to sleep. Check it out!

Bond Between Us

Bond Between Us is a tiny experimental game made for GGJ2020. Theme was repairing, so we designed a local multiplayer game in which two people, bond by a thread of light, will have to overcome obstacles together in order to repair their relationship. Available on: https://globalgamejam.org/2020/games/bond-between-us-4

Relaxing Cup

Diseñado en la Game Jam Madrid Crea. Tienes un pequeño puesto de café en la plaza Mayor de Madrid. Personajes madrileños varios, desde Carlos III a Penélope Cruz o el oso y el madroño, te pedirán comida y bebida. Tras atenderlos correctamente, ¡podrás interactuar con ellos y darles conversación! Disponible en https://leavemeal0ne.itch.io/relaxing-cup

My itch.io page

Check out some other projects I made for several game jams! https://leavemeal0ne.itch.io/

ABOUT

Hi! My name is Eva. I have been playing videogames my whole life, and I also wanted to make them from scratch! I studied videogame design and development, majoring in game design, to find that designing videogames was my passion. Making games that people enjoy and have fun with is awesome and I'm willing to learn how to do it better and better everytime! Contact me for more info!

I studied a 4-year degree, then a master's degree, both based in Madrid, along with several game design courses. I love nearly every aspect of game design, from level design to combat, AI design, narrative, and audio design! I made the music and the sounds for nearly every project I've participated in. I'm also a big game jam fan! I try to participate in every single one I can.
